Meet Angel, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Angel lives at <a href='/home/?user=angel_1001'>10020 Capital Avenue</a> in one of the tall waterside homes in Lakeview.  She has enjoyed fishing, boating, and swimming at Millsberry Lake since April 20, 2005.<br><br>Angel is perhaps best known in Millsberry for her generosity.  She's always ready to lend a hand whenever someone needs assistance.  Because she's so knowledgeable, Angel often stays after school to help other students with their homework.  Angel recently found a new way of combining her desire to aid others with her love of animals, by volunteering to take the dogs of her elderly neighbors out for walks in Lakeview or games of fetch in <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a>.  Angel's generosity can also be seen on the soccer field.  Despite her love of scoring the winning goal, Angel is always ready to unselfishly pass the ball to her teammates when needed.<br><br>In addition to being generous, Angel is also very creative.  Her favorite hobby is knitting, and Angel likes to experiment by making new and interesting things with her knitting needles and yarn.  She often spends afternoons in her tree house, busily knitting gifts for her friends.  Her favorite creation thus far has been the white, black, and light blue scarf that she made to keep herself warm during the long Millsberry winter.<br><br>Lately, Angel has been expressing her creativity in other ways.  She recently visited the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio/">Millsberry Recording Studio</a>, and while she was there, Angel decided to combine her favorite musical styles and record a few songs of her very own!  The result was an unusual yet interesting mixture of country, salsa, and classical music.  Millsberry residents soon became intrigued by the unique, special sound of Angel's music and quickly propelled one of her tracks to the top of the Cinnamon Toast Crunch Top Ten chart!<br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Angel, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week! </div>
